**Overall Meaning:**

"Know that ancient person, knowable through Vedanta, the soul of consciousness, the source of the universe, the great one. Knowing him alone, one goes beyond death. There is no other path for liberation."

**Explanation:**

This verse emphasizes the importance of knowing the ultimate reality, the Supreme Person, as the path to liberation. It describes this person as ancient, the source of all existence, and the embodiment of consciousness. By knowing this person, one transcends the cycle of birth and death and achieves liberation. The verse also stresses that this knowledge is the only path to liberation, and no other path exists.


